# FocusFlow Walkthrough

This document demonstrates the adaptive UI states of the FocusFlow application.

## 1. Beginner Mode
New users start in Beginner Mode, featuring a simplified interface and guided onboarding.

### Onboarding Carousel
Users are greeted with a 3-step carousel explaining the core concepts.
![Beginner Onboarding](/home/suix0/.gemini/antigravity/brain/6d935168-3b01-4824-9e53-5c25b7ecfa66/beginner_onboarding_1763891667077.png)

### Empty State & FAB
The main screen features a large Floating Action Button (FAB) and helpful tooltips to encourage the first action.
![Beginner Empty List](/home/suix0/.gemini/antigravity/brain/6d935168-3b01-4824-9e53-5c25b7ecfa66/beginner_empty_list_1763891695446.png)

## 2. Experienced Mode
After completing 5 tasks, the user is upgraded to Experienced Mode.

### Transition
A celebration toast notifies the user of the upgrade.
![Transition Toast](/home/suix0/.gemini/antigravity/brain/6d935168-3b01-4824-9e53-5c25b7ecfa66/experienced_transition_1763891865284.png)

### Dense UI & Quick Add
The interface shifts to a dark theme with a dense task list and a "Quick Add" bar at the top for rapid entry.
![Experienced List](/home/suix0/.gemini/antigravity/brain/6d935168-3b01-4824-9e53-5c25b7ecfa66/experienced_list_1763891881191.png)

## 3. Behavior-Based Adaptation
If the user misses 3 or more deadlines in the last 7 days, the app intervenes.

### Intervention Modal
A full-screen modal appears to help the user get back on track.
![Intervention Modal](/home/suix0/.gemini/antigravity/brain/6d935168-3b01-4824-9e53-5c25b7ecfa66/intervention_modal_fixed_1763891989898.png)

### Overdue Tasks
The user can choose to re-prioritize, viewing their overdue tasks clearly.
![Overdue Tasks](/home/suix0/.gemini/antigravity/brain/6d935168-3b01-4824-9e53-5c25b7ecfa66/overdue_tasks_1763891930467.png)
